				<wikidot:authorName>Whalerus</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3305725</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Very good read. Definitely has my +1. A small scientific critique is you should replace the uses of &quot;genome&quot; with &quot;chromosome&quot;. Genome refers to all of an organism's genes. Chromosomes are the pairs of packaged DNA. From the context in the article, chromosome is the term you want.</p> 
				 	]]>
