					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13575178#post-4727012</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13575178/scp-5512#post-4727012</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 23 Jul 2020 06:48:20 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Grigori Karpin</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4558017</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Thank you for the kind words, and the reasonable critique. I originally had personal logs from the POI revealing all his secrets&#8230; but <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mountaintimepunch" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2028454&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1595486900" alt="MountainTimePunch" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2028454)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mountaintimepunch" >MountainTimePunch</a></span> pointed out that it took him out of it to think of a crazy alien immortal thing writing a diary&#8230;</p> <p>So I thought maybe some of the propaganda to communicate world building things I wanted to include in 4612 but couldn't find a reasonable place for.</p> <p>Anyway sorry for the long response, thanks for reading!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13575178#post-4727007</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13575178/scp-5512#post-4727007</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 23 Jul 2020 06:43:02 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>RockTeethMothEyes</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4022320</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>There's some really good and cool lines in this. Of particular note</p> <blockquote> <p>People with guns are so quick to threaten violence, as if you invented it.</p> </blockquote> <p>this one. Each scene that takes place here is clear and communicates the atmosphere excellently. The one thing that I didn't care for is the excerpts of 5512-1. Not to say they don't have a place here, as they are clearly a component of the overall anomaly, but including these excerpts puts the brakes on the pacing. I don't find them particularly necessary to the story being told here.</p> <p>All-in-all, this is a marvelous piece and worthy of a +1.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
